/*! \mainpage Fundamental Vector Reduction/Transformation Operator (RTOp) Interfaces

This doxygen collection contains documentation for the fundamental RTOp
(reduction/transformation operators) interfaces which provides the basic
mechanism for implementing vector operations in a flexible and efficient
manner.

There is very little code that makes up these fundamental RTOp interfaces:

\section RTOp_interface_software_sec Software

<ul>

<li> Simple types:

  <ul>

  <li> Strided contiguous chunks for vector and multi-vector data

    <ul>
    <li> <tt>RTOpPack::ConstSubVectorView</tt>
    <li> <tt>RTOpPack::SubVectorView</tt>
    <li> <tt>RTOpPack::ConstSubMultiVectorView</tt>
    <li> <tt>RTOpPack::SubMultiVectorView</tt>
    </ul>

  <li> Exception types:

    <ul>
    <li> <tt>RTOpPack::IncompatibleVecs</tt>
    <li> <tt>RTOpPack::InvalidNumTargVecs</tt>
    <li> <tt>RTOpPack::InvalidNumVecs</tt>
    <li> <tt>RTOpPack::InvalidUsage</tt>
    <li> <tt>RTOpPack::UnknownError</tt>
    </ul>

  </ul>

<li> Abstract interface classes:

  <ul>

  <li> <tt>RTOpPack::RTOpT</tt>: Interface for a reduction/transformation operator
  <li> <tt>RTOpPack::ReductTarget</tt>: Opaque base class for reduction target objects

</ul>

\section RTOp_interface_links_sec Links

<ul>

<li> <a href="../../../../doc/html/index.html">Main RTOp package documentation page</a>

</ul>

*/
